25/05/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic and Serbia-Montenegrin counterpart Svetozar Marovic met on Monday (24 May) to discuss bilateral ties and Euro-Atlantic integration. 
Mesic said good neighbourly relations remain a foreign policy priority. 
The heads of state watched as a protocol on co-operation in the EU integration process was signed. 
Marovic is his country's first head of state to pay an official visit to Croatia following the break-up of Yugoslavia. 
(HINA, B92, BBC, AFP - 24/05/04)
